The President of the United States, in a statement, expressed his satisfaction and relief that Captain Phillips has been rescued and is safe on board the USS Boxer. He commended the efforts of the U.S. military and other departments and agencies involved in the rescue mission. The President emphasized the need to halt the rise of piracy in the region and stated that collaboration with partners, prevention of future attacks, interdiction of piracy acts, and holding the perpetrators accountable are crucial in achieving this goal. The President also praised Captain Phillips for his bravery and selflessness, stating that his courage serves as a model for all Americans.